<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="ITA51">
<l>matikkaṇṭāy neñcē maṇivaṇṇaṉ pāta</l>
<l>matikkaṇṭāy maṟṟavaṉpēr taṉṉai – matikkaṇṭāy</l>
<l>pērāḻi niṉṟu peyarntu kaṭalkaṭainta</l>
<l>nīrāḻi vaṇṇa ṉiṟam</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Envision mentally, heart, the feet of him with sapphire colour,</l>
<l>envision mentally, again, his names, envision mentally</l>
<l>the colour of him of water-ocean hue, who, coming from<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">Here might be one of the earliest passages where the absolutive niṉṟu is used to circumscribe an ablative, in a kind of postposition meaning “from”. </note></l>
<l>the great ocean, churned the [milk] sea.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
